## reg-names

**Value type:** `<stringlist>`

A list of strings providing names for the corresponding entries in the `reg` property. Each name identifies a named register region. The number of strings must equal the number of *(address, length)* pairs in the `reg` property.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi */
pcie0: pci@1c00000 {
    reg = <0x01c00000 0x3000>,
          <0x01c03000 0x1000>;
    reg-names = "parf", "phy";
};
```
